How many square units are in the area of the parallelogram with vertices at (0, 0), (6, 0), (2, 8) and (8, 8)? -------------------- 
[92mGround Truth:[0m
48 -------------------- 
[94mResponse:[0m
<reasoning>
To find the area of a parallelogram given we know its vertices, we can use the formula for the area of a parallelogram, which is given by \( A = \text{base} \times \text{height}_} \).

The base of the parallelogram can be calculated as the distance between two adjacent vertices. In this case, we choose the vertices (0, 0) and (6, 0). The distance between these points is 6 units.

The height of the parallelogram can be calculated as the vertical distance between the base and and the opposite side of the parallelogram. In this case, we choose the vertices (0, 0) and (8, 8). The distance between these points is 8 units.

Now, we can calculate the area of the parallelogram using the formula \( A = \text{base} \times \text{height} \):

\[ A = 6 \times 8 = 48 \]

Therefore, the area of the parallelogram is 48 square units.
</reasoning>

<answer>
48
</answer> -------------------- 
